        "slug": "step-10-how-profitable-is-your-business",
        "status": "publish",
        "type": "sfwd-lessons",
        "link": "https://community.tala.test/course/build-a-business-model/lessons/step-10-how-profitable-is-your-business/",
        "title": {
            "rendered": "Step 10: How profitable is your business?"
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "\n<p>To know your profits, you can use this calculation:&nbsp;<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Revenue (the money that comes into your business) &#8211; costs (what it takes to run your business)&nbsp; = profit (what you earn)&nbsp;</strong><br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If in July, Stanley brought in <strong>60,000 KSh</strong>, his profit would be <strong>24,200 KSh</strong>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>In August, Stanley has sold 346 fruit salads. His costs were 35,800 KSh. How many cups of juice would he also have to sell to make a profit of 10,000 KSH?</h2>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
