        "slug": "step-2-defining-your-value-proposition",
        "status": "publish",
        "type": "sfwd-lessons",
        "link": "https://community.tala.test/course/build-a-business-model/lessons/step-2-defining-your-value-proposition/",
        "title": {
            "rendered": "Step 2: Defining your value proposition"
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "\n<p>We want to begin with the center: the value proposition. This is the top box on your BMC.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>value proposition</strong> lists the benefits that your solution provides to your customers. <strong>Why</strong> do customers buy from you? What do they gain from your product/service? What makes your product or service better than others?<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Think back to your [customer] [challenge] [solution] model. To come up with your value proposition, make a list of all the benefits of your customers will get from using your solution.&nbsp;<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have a list of all the benefits, come up with one sentence summarizing them. This is your value proposition. <br><br>Got to the next step for an example.<br></p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
