        "slug": "step-4-understand-your-cost-structure",
        "status": "publish",
        "type": "sfwd-lessons",
        "link": "https://community.tala.test/course/build-a-business-model/lessons/step-4-understand-your-cost-structure/",
        "title": {
            "rendered": "Step 4: Understand your cost structure"
        },
        "content": {
            "rendered": "\n<p>A<strong> cost structure </strong>is a list of all expenses required to operate a business. The three things that determine your costs are your <strong>resources, activities </strong>and<strong> partnerships.&nbsp;</strong><br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Resources: </strong>What resources (equipment, supplies, land, etc.) does your business have or need to operate?&nbsp;<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Activities:</strong> What activities (cooking, building, delivering, training, etc.) do you have to do to create your product or service?&nbsp;<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Partnerships: </strong>Who else do you need to work with to make your business successful?¬† This could be vendors, your landlord, suppliers, employees, etc.¬†<br></p>\n",
            "protected": false
        },
